'''Mishima Shrine''' (???????) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Aono, {{ill|lt=Minamiizu|Q1203741|qid=Q1203741|1=Minamiizu}}, {{ill|lt=Kamo District|Q961511|qid=Q961511|1=Kamo District, Shizuoka}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Prefecture|Q131320|qid=Q131320|1=Shizuoka Prefecture}}<ref>[http://shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4401113 Mishima Shrine] - Shizuoka Prefecture Shrine Office</ref>.

=== Overview ===
It is located on the northern mountain foothills of the Aono district in the upper reaches of the Aono River, in northwestern Minamiizu.

Its founding is unknown, but it is a candidate shrine for the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} "Takeishitsuki-no-Mikoto Shrine" (??????????????), and an ancient shrine also recorded in the ''{{ill|lt=Izu no kuni jinjaich?|Q17193087|qid=Q17193087|1=Izu no kuni jinjaich?}}'' as "J?shi-i no J? Takeshi no My?jin"<ref name="gen">[https://genbu.net/data/izu/misima5_title.htm Mishima Shrine] - Genmatsushi</ref><ref name="engi">[http://engishiki.org/izu/bun/iz140123-04.html Mishima Shrine] - Study of Engishiki Shrines</ref>.

